  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_independent_mental_health_advocate">Independent Mental Health Advocate</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_independent_mental_health_advocate">Independent Mental Health Advocate</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_independent_mental_health_advocate">IMHA</xref>
) is a specialist mental health advocate, who helps 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 understand the legal provisions to which they are subject under the Mental Health Act.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_independent_mental_health_advocate">Independent Mental Health Advocates</xref>
, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 part of the 
    <xref href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/response-on-funding-allocations-for-independent-mental-health-services-and-the-treatment-of-armed-forces-compensation-in-charging-for-social-care"
            scope="external"
            format="html">gov.uk website.</xref>
  </p>

